# 🚀 Day 70 – Create the OCR Service (Project Architecture)

Welcome to **Day 70!**

Today we begin preparing your app for **real OCR integration**.

> **Important:** We are **not** connecting to Google Cloud Vision yet. Instead, we're building the project structure that will make integration much easier.

Professional apps separate responsibilities like this:

```text
Flutter UI
     │
     ▼
OCR Service
     │
     ▼
Google Cloud Vision API
     │
     ▼
Extracted Text
     │
     ▼
Blood Report Model
     │
     ▼
Report Screen
```

---

# 🎯 Today's Goal

By the end of today, your project will have a dedicated **services** folder and an `OCRService` class.

For now, it will return sample data. Later, we'll replace it with a real API call.

---

# Step 1

Create a new folder:

```text
lib/services
```

---

# Step 2

Inside it, create a file:

```text
ocr_service.dart
```

---

# Step 3

Paste this complete code into:

```text
lib/services/ocr_service.dart
```

```dart
import '../models/blood_report.dart';

class OCRService {

  Future<BloodReport> analyzeReport(String fileName) async {

    // Simulate OCR processing delay
    await Future.delayed(const Duration(seconds: 2));

    return BloodReport(
      patientName: "Srujan",
      bloodGroup: "B+",
      hemoglobin: 13.8,
      hba1c: 6.1,
      vitaminD: 18,
    );
  }

}
```

---

# What This Does

When we call:

```dart
OCRService service = OCRService();

BloodReport report =
    await service.analyzeReport("blood_report.pdf");
```

It returns a `BloodReport` object.

Right now the values are hard-coded.

Later we'll replace this part with:

```text
Upload Image/PDF
        ↓
Google Cloud Vision OCR
        ↓
Extract Text
        ↓
Convert to BloodReport
        ↓
Return Report
```

The rest of your app won't need to change.

---

# Project Structure

Your project should now look like:

```text
lib
│
├── models
│     ├── blood_report.dart
│     └── sample_report.dart
│
├── services
│     └── ocr_service.dart
│
├── screens
│     ├── login_screen.dart
│     ├── register_screen.dart
│     ├── dashboard_screen.dart
│     ├── upload_report_screen.dart
│     ├── upload_progress_screen.dart
│     └── report_details_screen.dart
```

---

# Why This Is Important

Many beginners put everything inside one screen:

```text
Screen
  ↓
OCR
Database
API
AI
UI
```

This quickly becomes difficult to maintain.

Instead, we're separating concerns:

* **models/** → Stores data.
* **screens/** → Displays data.
* **services/** → Performs work (OCR, AI, cloud, database).

This makes the code easier to understand and extend.

